56
00:06:11,940 --> 00:06:14,650
- What?
- I know why you're doing this.

57
00:06:14,650 --> 00:06:19,400
You came this far because of how you feel about her.

58
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:21,020
Insecurity.

59
00:06:21,020 --> 00:06:25,880
Because of that low and dark insecurity, you dragged me into this, didn't you?

60
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:30,110
Go on, Seung Gyu.

61
00:06:30,110 --> 00:06:36,530
But you can't become Ms. Seo even if you dress like her and steal her spot.

62
00:06:36,530 --> 00:06:39,470
Because you're just Kwon Yun Jin.

63
00:08:56,500 --> 00:08:58,100
Excuse me.

64
00:09:02,340 --> 00:09:04,670
- You can't.
- No!

65
00:09:18,760 --> 00:09:22,020
- Don't look.
- Te Oh, Te Oh, is that Seung Gyu?

66
00:09:22,020 --> 00:09:25,020
Te Oh! Is that Seung Gyu?

67
00:09:25,020 --> 00:09:26,730
- T-Te Oh!
- Ms. Seo.

68
00:09:26,730 --> 00:09:28,270
Yun Te Oh!

69
00:09:28,270 --> 00:09:29,760
Ms. Seo.

70
00:10:07,370 --> 00:10:09,150
I'm sorry.

71
00:10:39,770 --> 00:10:41,580
Go upstairs.

72
00:10:42,610 --> 00:10:45,990
[For the one who's hesitating / My Santiago]

73
00:10:49,470 --> 00:10:52,290
Yes, Sunbae. Nam Tae Ju isn't here.

74
00:10:52,290 --> 00:10:54,070
Hello.

75
00:11:10,250 --> 00:11:14,360
You probably need to rest more.

76
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:16,860
Are you sure you'd be okay?

77
00:11:16,860 --> 00:11:21,180
Someone just died.

78
00:11:25,210 --> 00:11:28,400
Let's try piecing things together.

79
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:34,250
Nam Tae Ju told you where Baek Seung Gyu was.

80
00:11:34,250 --> 00:11:36,820
So, you went there and talked to him,

81
00:11:36,820 --> 00:11:42,490
but Nam Tae Ju suddenly barged in and killed Mr. Baek.

82
00:11:43,370 --> 00:11:46,420
And he tried to kill you, too. Is that correct?

83
00:11:47,890 --> 00:11:52,700
- Yes.
- Why did you go see Mr. Baek?

84
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:58,370
I just wanted to have a conversation.

85
00:11:58,370 --> 00:12:01,580
Let's talk about the motive.

86
00:12:01,580 --> 00:12:07,150
Coincidentally, something similar happened when you visited Mr. Baek last time.

87
00:12:07,150 --> 00:12:09,540
I think Mr. Baek...

88
00:12:10,540 --> 00:12:17,310
must've felt threatened by just seeing you.

89
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:22,260
Are you...

90
00:12:23,220 --> 00:12:26,440
suspicious of me right now?

91
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:30,750
Can you say that after seeing me like this?

92
00:12:32,470 --> 00:12:36,360
When I think about all the threats I got from Nam Tae Ju...

93
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:38,830
Nam Tae Ju...

94
00:12:38,830 --> 00:12:42,340
He tried to kill both Seung Gyu and me

95
00:12:42,340 --> 00:12:46,340
to cover up everything he's done so far.

96
00:12:46,340 --> 00:12:49,260
Can't you tell, Detective?

97
00:12:49,260 --> 00:12:52,540
Oh, I see.

98
00:13:44,300 --> 00:13:46,900
[Baek Seung Gyu]
Seung Gyu...

99
00:13:48,170 --> 00:13:51,380
I should've been by your side.

100
00:14:16,770 --> 00:14:19,370
How dare you show up here?

101
00:14:19,370 --> 00:14:21,790
How dare you show up here?

102
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:27,470
I came because I felt guilty that I couldn't stop it.

103
00:14:28,940 --> 00:14:31,300
Do you really mean it?

104
00:14:33,610 --> 00:14:35,590
I mean it.

105
00:14:39,290 --> 00:14:41,110
Kwon Yun Jin.

106
00:14:42,650 --> 00:14:45,330
No secrets last forever.

107
00:14:46,310 --> 00:14:47,990
I'm leaving.

108
00:15:10,450 --> 00:15:15,560
The fingerprints from the kitchen knife turned out to be Nam Tae Ju's.

109
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:18,450
I checked the transaction history, too.

110
00:15:18,450 --> 00:15:23,150
As Ms. Kwon said, he received more than one billion won.

111
00:15:23,150 --> 00:15:26,540
How about his whereabouts? Does he have an alibi?

112
00:15:26,540 --> 00:15:31,830
He was captured on the CCTV near the scene on the night of the incident.

113
00:15:31,830 --> 00:15:35,550
He's nowhere to be found currently.

114
00:15:36,660 --> 00:15:38,470
No way.

115
00:15:38,470 --> 00:15:40,090
Did Nam Tae Ju really...

116
00:15:40,090 --> 00:15:44,560
The evidence is pointing at him. What can we do?

117
00:15:44,560 --> 00:15:48,960
Why did he leave the only evidence at the scene?

118
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:51,080
H-How dare you talk to me like that?

119
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:53,470
- What will you do about it?
- So what if you're older?

120
00:15:53,470 --> 00:15:55,990
You should've used the turn signal if you were on the right.

121
00:15:55,990 --> 00:15:57,300
You cut me in first!

122
00:15:57,300 --> 00:15:58,700
Is that how you drive?

123
00:15:58,700 --> 00:16:00,290
Gosh, seriously.

124
00:16:00,290 --> 00:16:02,140
- Can't you drive properly?
- How dare you talk casually?

125
00:16:02,140 --> 00:16:03,810
- Can't you?
- Who cares if you're older?

126
00:16:03,810 --> 00:16:05,420
I care.

127
00:16:11,880 --> 00:16:13,300
Yes.

128
00:16:20,670 --> 00:16:23,820
He doesn't gamble or anything like that.

129
00:16:27,030 --> 00:16:29,880
No, I really had no idea.

130
00:16:34,060 --> 00:16:36,230
Did everything go well?

131
00:16:37,920 --> 00:16:39,670
What do we do?

132
00:16:39,670 --> 00:16:41,490
Shouldn't we talk to Jae Won?

133
00:16:41,490 --> 00:16:42,750
No.

134
00:16:43,580 --> 00:16:44,960
Don't you try to call her.

135
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:46,670
Unbelievable.

136
00:16:46,670 --> 00:16:48,820
Stop worrying about your daughter and worry about yourself, Oppa.

137
00:16:48,820 --> 00:16:50,910
She's the only one who could help you.

138
00:16:50,910 --> 00:16:53,050
Don't be ridiculous.

139
00:16:53,050 --> 00:16:55,730
Will you spend the rest of your life in prison?

140
00:16:55,730 --> 00:16:58,140
They said murder!

141
00:17:11,140 --> 00:17:14,480
Hand me the evidence you have.

142
00:17:14,480 --> 00:17:17,150
What are you talking about? What evidence?

143
00:17:17,150 --> 00:17:22,880
I'm sure you left evidence while cleaning up after...

144
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:25,660
Kwon Yeong Ik and Kwon Yun Jin.

145
00:17:27,220 --> 00:17:29,790
You knew I'd come,

146
00:17:30,810 --> 00:17:33,470
but you don't know the reason.

147
00:17:35,030 --> 00:17:38,130
You're disposable, too, after all.

148
00:17:38,130 --> 00:17:40,790
You'll be thrown out as well.

149
00:17:40,790 --> 00:17:42,900
Come to me, then.

150
00:17:48,370 --> 00:17:50,060
[2023 Investigation report for Baek Seung Gyu's fall incident]

151
00:18:03,370 --> 00:18:05,020
Is it tasty?

152
00:18:06,380 --> 00:18:09,190
You look better since you're on a leave.

153
00:18:09,190 --> 00:18:11,090
What brings you here?

154
00:18:11,090 --> 00:18:13,610
You heard about Nam Tae Ju, right?

155
00:18:13,610 --> 00:18:15,500
Yes. Well...

156
00:18:15,500 --> 00:18:16,950
Tell me...

157
00:18:17,900 --> 00:18:21,880
what happened when you were on the Baek Seung Gyu case.

158
00:18:21,880 --> 00:18:24,150
If you don't want to lose your job immediately.

159
00:18:26,220 --> 00:18:27,470
I'll get going now.

160
00:18:27,470 --> 00:18:31,210
Come on. Don't do anything silly.

161
00:18:39,770 --> 00:18:43,580
If I tell you right now,

162
00:18:43,580 --> 00:18:46,080
I'd no longer be a part of it, right?

163
00:18:46,080 --> 00:18:49,150
Were you ever? Sit down.

164
00:18:55,410 --> 00:18:58,060
Nam sunbae knew...

165
00:18:58,060 --> 00:19:01,660
Kwon Yun Jin pushed him but tried to cover it up. He said nothing would happen.

166
00:19:01,660 --> 00:19:04,000
Yes, he covered it up.

167
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:06,190
But why would he kill him?

168
00:19:06,190 --> 00:19:09,810
- Pardon?
- Why did he have a falling out with Kwon Yun Jin?

169
00:19:09,810 --> 00:19:14,620
Well, I don't know much about it.

170
00:19:14,620 --> 00:19:20,430
But it seemed Nam sunbae and Kwon Yun Jin were pretty close.

171
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:23,160
You can reach Nam Tae Ju, right?

172
00:19:23,160 --> 00:19:26,290
I tried contacting him already,

173
00:19:26,290 --> 00:19:27,680
but his phone is off.

174
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:30,870
Let me know if you hear from him.

175
00:19:30,870 --> 00:19:32,260
Where are you going?

176
00:19:32,260 --> 00:19:38,610
We'll discuss your future extensively after this is done.

177
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:41,680
You're prepared for it, right?

178
00:19:46,440 --> 00:19:48,120
Shit.

179
00:19:50,260 --> 00:19:52,930
I found this while doing research on Nam Tae Ju.

180
00:19:57,040 --> 00:19:58,530
[A gambling group of 15 people, including a police officer, were arrested]

181
00:20:03,040 --> 00:20:04,420
What's wrong?

182
00:20:05,320 --> 00:20:07,920
I see another familiar face.

183
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:09,440
Who is it?

184
00:20:10,850 --> 00:20:12,900
My mom.

185
00:20:12,900 --> 00:20:14,350
[Evidence No. 9]

186
00:20:14,350 --> 00:20:16,970
[Evidence No. 2]

187
00:20:18,690 --> 00:20:20,690
I swear I was just watching.

188
00:20:20,690 --> 00:20:22,950
It was my first time day, okay?

189
00:20:22,950 --> 00:20:24,940
- I really didn't do it.
- You did.

190
00:20:24,940 --> 00:20:27,100
I swear I didn't.

191
00:20:30,210 --> 00:20:32,950
You can't smoke in here. No smoking.

192
00:20:38,210 --> 00:20:39,340
Aigoo.

193
00:20:39,340 --> 00:20:41,570
[Criminal record]
How impressive. Seriously.

194
00:20:41,570 --> 00:20:43,360
Why do you gamble?

195
00:20:43,360 --> 00:20:46,170
Do you really think you could win money?

196
00:20:46,170 --> 00:20:50,250
Do you know who Seo Jae Won is?

197
00:20:50,250 --> 00:20:52,430
Who's that?

198
00:20:52,430 --> 00:20:55,280
Look her up if you're curious.

199
00:20:59,560 --> 00:21:02,820
[Seo Jae Won]

200
00:21:06,650 --> 00:21:08,980
She's...

201
00:21:08,980 --> 00:21:11,740
my daughter.

202
00:21:11,740 --> 00:21:13,350
Excuse me.

203
00:21:18,130 --> 00:21:20,620
You need to come back when you receive the notice of attendance.

204
00:21:20,620 --> 00:21:23,400
Otherwise, I'll come to you with a warrant.

205
00:21:29,830 --> 00:21:31,360
What's that?

206
00:21:38,080 --> 00:21:40,440
Stop by to lift up your mood.

207
00:21:56,020 --> 00:21:57,550
[The police are searching for Nam, a man in his 40s who murdered a man in his 30s]

208
00:21:57,550 --> 00:21:59,170
Did they have to use this photo?

209
00:21:59,170 --> 00:22:01,260
[Murder suspect wanted]

210
00:22:01,260 --> 00:22:03,080
Would people recognize me?

211
00:22:10,460 --> 00:22:11,590
Hello, sir.

212
00:22:11,590 --> 00:22:13,820
Yes, hello.

213
00:22:16,470 --> 00:22:18,310
You've been here for a long time.

214
00:22:19,310 --> 00:22:22,250
- I have a lot to think about.
- I see.

215
00:22:22,250 --> 00:22:25,860
I used to come here often with my wife.

216
00:22:25,860 --> 00:22:27,070
It's a nice spot.

217
00:22:27,070 --> 00:22:29,320
Oh, I see.

218
00:22:29,320 --> 00:22:32,070
Were you able to sort out your thoughts?

219
00:22:32,070 --> 00:22:33,940
I'm still deliberating.

220
00:22:34,800 --> 00:22:36,720
I'll leave you to it, then.

221
00:22:36,720 --> 00:22:38,790
I hope you catch a lot.

222
00:22:41,330 --> 00:22:43,560
I'm deliberating on...

223
00:22:45,230 --> 00:22:47,750
whether I should kill or let go.

224
00:22:51,230 --> 00:22:53,100
Today's topic of Hot Issue Today is

225
00:22:53,100 --> 00:22:57,740
related to Seo Jae Won, who left the mental institute recently.

226
00:22:57,740 --> 00:23:02,110
We'll be talking about her father, Seo Chang Seok specifically.

227
00:23:02,110 --> 00:23:04,360
Would you believe me if I said...

228
00:23:04,360 --> 00:23:09,360
he murdered his wife using pesticide to get insurance money?

229
00:23:09,360 --> 00:23:12,990
[Seo Jae Won's father poisoned his wife for an insurance payout?]
We'll delve into this shocking story...

230
00:23:13,940 --> 00:23:18,500
It's a scoop you'd be quite interested in.

231
00:23:19,450 --> 00:23:23,330
But I get to decide when to release it.

232
00:23:28,790 --> 00:23:32,290
According to the information I acquired secretly,

233
00:23:32,290 --> 00:23:35,630
Mr. Seo Chang Seok was arrested this morning.

234
00:23:35,630 --> 00:23:40,490
This case was revealed thanks to Hot Issue Today's quick investigation...

235
00:23:40,490 --> 00:23:43,050
I'm sorry. I'm a bit late.

236
00:23:43,050 --> 00:23:45,420
Let's go to your father right now.

237
00:23:45,420 --> 00:23:47,710
No, I won't go.

238
00:23:47,710 --> 00:23:49,680
What are you saying? Didn't you see the article?

239
00:23:49,680 --> 00:23:52,680
I did. I watched Reporter Choi's YouTube video, too.

240
00:23:52,700 --> 00:23:55,800
You should go right now, then. Aren't you worried about your father?

241
00:23:55,850 --> 00:23:59,760
He hasn't contacted me the entire time he was being questioned.

242
00:24:01,010 --> 00:24:03,380
He doesn't want me to come.

243
00:24:03,380 --> 00:24:05,440
How can you be sure about that?

244
00:24:07,740 --> 00:24:09,760
Because I was like that.

245
00:24:16,980 --> 00:24:19,170
Attorney, did you arrive safely?

246
00:24:19,170 --> 00:24:22,430
Yes, I did.

247
00:24:22,430 --> 00:24:24,460
How's my dad doing?

248
00:24:24,460 --> 00:24:27,250
He's enduring it well.

249
00:24:27,250 --> 00:24:29,090
That's a relief.

250
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:33,340
Tell him I'm enduring it well, too.

251
00:24:33,340 --> 00:24:37,460
And we'll see each other in good health soon.

252
00:24:37,460 --> 00:24:38,880
Please take good care of him.

253
00:24:38,880 --> 00:24:42,210
Okay, I will. Don't worry.

254
00:25:22,650 --> 00:25:24,820
I'm relieved that...

255
00:25:25,820 --> 00:25:28,620
you look better than I expected.

256
00:25:30,500 --> 00:25:32,530
How is...

257
00:25:33,530 --> 00:25:34,770
your mom doing?

258
00:25:34,770 --> 00:25:37,080
She's doing well.

259
00:25:40,090 --> 00:25:42,760
By the way, I'm surprised.

260
00:25:42,760 --> 00:25:46,380
You know how to ask how someone's doing.

261
00:25:47,940 --> 00:25:52,060
There was an article recently.

262
00:25:54,100 --> 00:25:56,390
Do you know, by chance?

263
00:25:56,390 --> 00:25:58,960
- Did you do it?
- Gosh.

264
00:25:58,960 --> 00:26:01,380
I'm so disappointed.

265
00:26:02,340 --> 00:26:05,210
I don't expect you to worry,

266
00:26:06,210 --> 00:26:11,020
but should you be asking your daughter if she's the culprit?

